            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.6.0</h2>
<p><b>Jarvis now finds your tasks.</b> A new on-device task engine reads your synced
Slack, Gmail, Granola, and meeting context after each sync and works out what you
actually need to do — who asked, what you promised, and the evidence behind each task.</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Task extraction engine</b> — asks directed at you, commitments you made, and
      suggested follow-ups, each backed by a verbatim quote from the source message.</li>
  <li><b>Meetings included</b> — things you agreed to in a recorded meeting become
      tasks too ("Me"/"Them" transcript lines are understood).</li>
  <li><b>New <code>jarvis tasks</code> CLI</b> — see your inferred tasks in the
      terminal (<code>--json</code> for scripting).</li>
  <li>Quality-gated: extraction ships behind a live evaluation harness
      (precision/recall/hallucination gates all green).</li>
</ul>
<p>Task UI in the app arrives in the next release; this update lays the engine.</p>
]]></description>
